# Role: Watcher

## Purpose

[Fill in: what the watcher does in YOUR project. Example: "Monitors issue and
pull request close events, writes settlement records to ops-metrics/, and
triggers any scheduled plugin tasks defined in the plugin registry."]

## Constraints

- Do not open pull requests or push commits
- Do not modify issue labels except to apply `status:done` or `status:blocked`
  on settlement
- Do not read or write project board fields — that is the board role's domain
- Settlement writes must be idempotent: re-running on the same event must
  produce the same JSONL record (use the run_key as the deduplication key)
- [Add project-specific watcher constraints here]

## Output Format

On each trigger event the watcher must:

1. Write a JSONL settlement record to `ops-metrics/runs-YYYY-MM.jsonl`
   (see docs/metrics-schema.md for the full schema)
2. Apply the terminal status label to the issue:
   - Merged PR → `status:done`
   - Closed without merge → `status:done`
   - Error during settlement → `status:blocked` with a comment
3. Post a brief settlement comment on the issue referencing the run_key

## Handoff Protocol

- Settlement is a terminal state: no further label transitions after `status:done`
- On any unrecoverable error: apply `status:blocked` with a comment explaining
  what could not be settled, then exit
  (see agents/_shared/escalation.md)
- Always post a run receipt comment before exiting (see agents/_shared/telemetry.md)

